  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Grant Aid in Response to the Humanitarian Crisis in Armenia and Azerbaijan Due to Nagorno-Karabakh Conflict</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With this project, IOM is providing immediate response to address the needs of displaced populations affected by the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict in Armenia through the in-kind provision of critical shelter/non-food item assistance. Activities include procurement, delivery, and provision of hygiene kits inclusive of menstrual hygiene management items to 2,300 persons displaced from Nagorno-Karabakh. Additionally, IOM is addressing the immediate needs of those staying in collective centres and ensuring basic improvements for up to three selected collective centres hosting total up to 200 persons to ensure dignified living conditions.</narrative>
  </description>
